WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.203 --> 00:00:04.514
<i>MALE NARRATOR:
Previously on</i> Prison Break:

2
00:00:04.538 --> 00:00:06.016
I didn't kill that man. Michael.

3
00:00:06.040 --> 00:00:07.240
The evidence says you did.

4
00:00:07.290 --> 00:00:08.423
I was set up.

5
00:00:08.492 --> 00:00:10.376
(GUN FIRES)

6
00:00:10.444 --> 00:00:11.960
<i>Put down your weapon.</i>

7
00:00:12.029 --> 00:00:14.557
I find it incumbent that you
see the inside of a prison cell.

8
00:00:14.581 --> 00:00:15.726
MICHAEL: I'm
looking for someone.

9
00:00:15.750 --> 00:00:16.809
A guy named Lincoln Burrows.

10
00:00:16.833 --> 00:00:18.645
SUCRE: Man killed the
Vice President's brother.

11
00:00:18.669 --> 00:00:20.212
Why you want to see
Burrows so bad anyhow?

12
00:00:20.236 --> 00:00:21.347
<i>MICHAEL: Because
he's my brother.</i>

13
00:00:21.371 --> 00:00:22.571
I'm getting you out of here.

14
00:00:22.606 --> 00:00:23.722
It's impossible.

15
00:00:23.791 --> 00:00:25.741
Not if you designed
the place. it isn't.

16
00:00:25.810 --> 00:00:28.059
You've seen the
blueprints. Better than that.

17
00:00:28.128 --> 00:00:29.894
I've got them on me.

18
00:00:29.963 --> 00:00:31.541
You find out who's
trying to bury him.

19
00:00:31.565 --> 00:00:32.914
Nobody's trying to bury him.

20
00:00:32.983 --> 00:00:34.366
The evidence was cooked.

21
00:00:34.434 --> 00:00:35.812
There's a lawyer poking around.

22
00:00:35.836 --> 00:00:38.203
Anyone that's a
threat is expendable.

23
00:00:38.272 --> 00:00:40.199
BELLICK: Scofield.
Found you a new cellie.

24
00:00:40.223 --> 00:00:41.439
Haywire. get in here.

25
00:00:41.492 --> 00:00:43.058
Someone found Fibonacci.

26
00:00:43.127 --> 00:00:44.309
Who was this someone?

27
00:00:44.378 --> 00:00:46.010
Now. where is Fibonacci?

28
00:00:46.079 --> 00:00:48.580
I give you that
information. I'm a dead man.

29
00:00:48.632 --> 00:00:49.714
Three.

30
00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:57.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

31
00:01:11.488 --> 00:01:12.621
On your feet.

32
00:01:14.141 --> 00:01:15.574
What time is it?

33
00:01:16.510 --> 00:01:17.653
BELLICK: Get up.

34
00:01:17.677 --> 00:01:18.861
LINCOLN: What's going on?

35
00:01:18.929 --> 00:01:20.239
Let's go. Lincoln. On your feet.

36
00:01:20.263 --> 00:01:21.447
No! Bellick!

37
00:01:21.515 --> 00:01:22.848
Come on. Move it.

38
00:01:22.900 --> 00:01:24.750
Bellick! Bellick!

39
00:01:24.818 --> 00:01:27.468
No! Bellick! Bellick!

40
00:01:27.537 --> 00:01:28.904
No. no!

41
00:01:30.257 --> 00:01:32.091
Bellick. where you taking...

42
00:01:32.159 --> 00:01:33.642
Bellick. no!

43
00:01:34.945 --> 00:01:37.012
No. Bellick. no. Bellick. no.

44
00:01:37.080 --> 00:01:39.298
I got a month left. Please!

45
00:01:39.366 --> 00:01:41.516
No. Bellick!

46
00:01:41.585 --> 00:01:42.918
Bellick. no!

47
00:01:42.986 --> 00:01:44.247
Bellick. please. Pull it up!

48
00:01:44.271 --> 00:01:47.573
No! No! I got a
month left! Please!

49
00:01:48.976 --> 00:01:50.058
Bellick!

50
00:01:51.111 --> 00:01:52.494
(MUTTERING)

51
00:01:54.130 --> 00:01:56.548
Please. Bellick.

52
00:02:02.205 --> 00:02:03.855
(HYPERVENTILATING)

53
00:02:16.069 --> 00:02:17.669
(PANTING)

54
00:02:23.594 --> 00:02:25.427
Make your peace. Lincoln.

55
00:02:32.602 --> 00:02:33.969
Let's get on with it.

56
00:03:12.392 --> 00:03:13.592
(CELL DOOR OPENS)

57
00:03:21.802 --> 00:03:23.318
GUARD: Open on 40!

58
00:03:33.030 --> 00:03:34.295
Close 40.

59
00:03:46.543 --> 00:03:50.111
Haywire. you ever
thought of breaking out?

60
00:03:50.180 --> 00:03:52.260
What the hell
would I do out there?

61
00:03:52.816 --> 00:03:54.516
Not be here.

62
00:03:54.585 --> 00:03:56.150
Halfway houses.

63
00:03:56.219 --> 00:03:57.752
Psych visits. Meds.

64
00:03:57.821 --> 00:03:59.554
Checking in with a PO.

65
00:03:59.623 --> 00:04:01.255
Urine tests.

66
00:04:01.324 --> 00:04:02.824
Keeping a job.

67
00:04:03.293 --> 00:04:04.359
No.

68
00:04:05.161 --> 00:04:06.895
Why you ask?

69
00:04:06.964 --> 00:04:09.075
This guy was talking about
it in the yard yesterday.

70
00:04:09.099 --> 00:04:10.499
I didn't know what to say.

71
00:04:10.567 --> 00:04:12.700
Tell Officer Bellick.

72
00:04:12.769 --> 00:04:13.846
(SCOFFS)

73
00:04:13.870 --> 00:04:15.990
He'll make life
easy for you if. uh...

74
00:04:20.977 --> 00:04:22.143
If what?

75
00:04:23.313 --> 00:04:24.630
Your tattoos.

76
00:04:25.149 --> 00:04:26.548
What about them?

77
00:04:28.485 --> 00:04:30.151
What are they of?

78
00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:32.365
No. no. no. What... what are
they? Like some kind of a...

79
00:04:32.389 --> 00:04:33.589
They're just tattoos.

80
00:04:33.623 --> 00:04:35.463
(TAPS ON CELL)
Candy time. Haywire.

81
00:04:40.981 --> 00:04:44.499
They think I have schizoaffective
disorder with bipolar tendencies.

82
00:04:44.567 --> 00:04:45.950
They think you got it?

83
00:04:47.887 --> 00:04:49.071
Whatever.

84
00:04:55.912 --> 00:04:58.596
I take the pills to keep
the quacks off my back.

85
00:05:04.053 --> 00:05:05.720
Bye. now.

86
00:05:05.789 --> 00:05:07.306
Get out of the way.

87
00:05:15.916 --> 00:05:17.059
You know. maybe they give you

88
00:05:17.083 --> 00:05:18.945
(TOILET FLUSHING)
those things for a reason.

89
00:05:18.969 --> 00:05:20.301
Yeah.

90
00:05:20.370 --> 00:05:22.370
To keep me dull.

91
00:05:22.439 --> 00:05:26.174
To keep me in their
invisible freaking handcuffs.

92
00:05:26.242 --> 00:05:28.910
Seriously. though. those
tattoos. they're beautiful.

93
00:05:28.996 --> 00:05:30.628
You mind if I. you know.

94
00:05:30.697 --> 00:05:32.197
look at the whole thing?

95
00:05:32.249 --> 00:05:34.049
I do. actually.

96
00:05:35.201 --> 00:05:36.417
Why?

97
00:05:36.486 --> 00:05:38.636
MAN: Door. Stand clear.

98
00:05:38.706 --> 00:05:41.106
Does there need to be a reason?

99
00:05:48.498 --> 00:05:50.331
Sucre.

100
00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:52.167
I'm not even
talking to you. man.

101
00:05:52.235 --> 00:05:53.768
(PRISONERS CHATTERING)

102
00:06:31.658 --> 00:06:33.191
ABRUZZI: What's the problem?

103
00:06:34.077 --> 00:06:35.710
Nothing I can't handle.

104
00:06:35.779 --> 00:06:37.378
Well. I knew there
was a problem.

105
00:06:37.447 --> 00:06:41.048
I could tell by looking at
you from across the yard.

106
00:06:41.117 --> 00:06:44.552
Guys. didn't I say
there was a problem?

107
00:06:44.621 --> 00:06:45.987
So. what's the problem?

108
00:06:47.073 --> 00:06:48.306
You're looking at it.

109
00:06:50.176 --> 00:06:51.943
What. Haywire? Yep.

110
00:06:52.011 --> 00:06:53.695
He's my new cellmate.

111
00:06:55.365 --> 00:06:57.498
That's a problem.
He doesn't sleep.

112
00:06:57.567 --> 00:06:59.017
So when do you dig?

113
00:06:59.085 --> 00:07:00.869
I don't.

114
00:07:00.937 --> 00:07:04.288
Hey. you and I are in bed now.

115
00:07:04.357 --> 00:07:06.290
You made me a promise. You said

116
00:07:06.359 --> 00:07:08.259
that we were gonna
get out of here.

117
00:07:08.328 --> 00:07:10.895
You renege now.
and I'm gonna cut you.

118
00:07:12.098 --> 00:07:14.449
So you better take
care of your business.

119
00:07:14.518 --> 00:07:16.101
or I will take care of you.

120
00:07:17.704 --> 00:07:18.953
Have a nice day.

121
00:08:06.820 --> 00:08:08.820
It's really coming
together. isn't it?

122
00:08:10.090 --> 00:08:12.502
Yep. You think it'll
be done in time?

123
00:08:12.526 --> 00:08:13.892
Well.

124
00:08:13.961 --> 00:08:17.073
I figure we still have the interior
alcoves and pilasters to do.

125
00:08:17.097 --> 00:08:20.131
which is no small
task. But. yes.

126
00:08:20.767 --> 00:08:21.967
I think so.

127
00:08:23.436 --> 00:08:25.403
Listen. I have to say. I...

128
00:08:25.472 --> 00:08:30.141
I really appreciate all the
effort that you put into this. Uh...

129
00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:32.544
I wish there was
some way I could.

130
00:08:32.613 --> 00:08:35.079
you know. pay you or something.

131
00:08:35.148 --> 00:08:37.468
There is one thing
you could do for me.

132
00:08:39.269 --> 00:08:40.935
My cellmate.

133
00:08:41.004 --> 00:08:44.405
Ah. the inimitable
Charles Patoshik. Haywire.

134
00:08:44.474 --> 00:08:46.057
Then you know.

135
00:08:46.126 --> 00:08:47.642
Hold it right there.

136
00:08:47.710 --> 00:08:50.561
Officer Bellick is in
charge of cell transfers.

137
00:08:50.630 --> 00:08:52.614
You're gonna have to
talk to him about that.

138
00:08:52.682 --> 00:08:55.983
I tried. but he seems to
think we're a good match.

139
00:08:56.052 --> 00:08:57.952
Did he threaten you? Who?

140
00:08:58.021 --> 00:08:59.487
Haywire or Bellick?

141
00:09:01.708 --> 00:09:04.476
Unfortunately. unless there's
some evidence of violence

142
00:09:04.544 --> 00:09:08.012
or sexual predation
between cellmates.

143
00:09:08.081 --> 00:09:12.166
those kinds of requests fall
on deaf ears around here.

144
00:09:12.235 --> 00:09:14.201
The prison system's
a little too crowded

145
00:09:14.270 --> 00:09:17.255
for requests based
on personality.

146
00:09:17.323 --> 00:09:19.290
It's not exactly
Sandals out there.

147
00:09:19.359 --> 00:09:20.508
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

148
00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:25.296
Warden. sorry.

149
00:09:25.364 --> 00:09:26.831
Your wife is here.

150
00:09:26.883 --> 00:09:28.383
What?

151
00:09:28.452 --> 00:09:31.553
She's not supposed
to be here till 4:00.

152
00:09:31.621 --> 00:09:34.823
Becky. do not let her come in
here under any circumstances.

153
00:09:34.891 --> 00:09:37.269
She's not supposed to see
this until our anniversary.

154
00:09:37.293 --> 00:09:38.493
I'll be right out.

155
00:09:43.050 --> 00:09:44.315
(CLEARS THROAT)

156
00:09:45.969 --> 00:09:47.535
Hi. sweetheart.

157
00:09:47.603 --> 00:09:49.003
You're early.

158
00:09:49.072 --> 00:09:50.504
Uh.

159
00:09:50.573 --> 00:09:53.240
Let's go eat.
You're acting funny.

160
00:09:53.309 --> 00:09:55.660
I am? What's going on in there?

161
00:09:55.712 --> 00:09:58.646
Oh. just going over some files.

162
00:09:58.715 --> 00:10:00.682
Becky said you
were in a meeting.

163
00:10:02.302 --> 00:10:04.736
This isn't Toledo
all over again. is it?

164
00:10:05.505 --> 00:10:06.938
Toledo?

165
00:10:07.007 --> 00:10:09.006
How can you say that?

166
00:10:09.075 --> 00:10:10.552
Then you won't mind if I look.

167
00:10:10.576 --> 00:10:11.776
Uh. Judy...

168
00:10:13.579 --> 00:10:16.331
Warden. I'm not going
to be able to cooperate.

169
00:10:16.400 --> 00:10:18.333
I'd get killed if I did.

170
00:10:19.552 --> 00:10:21.318
Johnson's still deciding.

171
00:10:22.705 --> 00:10:24.155
Then you and I are done.

172
00:10:27.994 --> 00:10:30.194
You should've just told me.

173
00:10:30.263 --> 00:10:31.863
Well. you... you know
how anxious I get

174
00:10:31.931 --> 00:10:33.575
when you come
around the inmates.

175
00:10:33.599 --> 00:10:35.432
Becky. have a
guard escort Johnson

176
00:10:35.501 --> 00:10:37.669
back to his cell. I'll
deal with him later.

177
00:10:37.737 --> 00:10:38.970
Come on. let's go eat.

178
00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:57.889
What are you doing
here? I'm your attorney.

179
00:10:59.625 --> 00:11:01.359
I'm representing you now.

180
00:11:02.228 --> 00:11:03.912
Hmm.

181
00:11:03.980 --> 00:11:05.746
If that's all right with you.

182
00:11:08.435 --> 00:11:10.969
Last time I saw you.
you called me a liar.

183
00:11:11.038 --> 00:11:12.603
Things have changed.

184
00:11:13.322 --> 00:11:15.156
I believe you now.

185
00:11:29.372 --> 00:11:33.324
I got in touch with Crab
Simmons' ex-girlfriend. Leticia.

186
00:11:33.393 --> 00:11:35.493
She corroborated your story.

187
00:11:37.064 --> 00:11:38.646
Will she testify?

188
00:11:38.732 --> 00:11:41.082
She's missing.

189
00:11:41.151 --> 00:11:43.851
I don't know. I think the
Secret Service got to her.

190
00:11:43.920 --> 00:11:45.019
Secret Service?

191
00:11:45.105 --> 00:11:46.371
They've been poking around.

192
00:11:46.440 --> 00:11:48.051
As soon as they show
up. she disappears.

193
00:11:48.075 --> 00:11:49.275
What do you think happened?

194
00:11:49.325 --> 00:11:51.176
Oh.

195
00:11:51.244 --> 00:11:53.945
I didn't realize it was
that high up. you know.

196
00:11:55.715 --> 00:11:57.565
Do you know what
we're up against?

197
00:11:57.634 --> 00:12:01.218
I know it's a lot more than either
of us can handle on our own.

198
00:12:01.805 --> 00:12:03.855
Project Justice.

199
00:12:03.923 --> 00:12:05.256
Why have I heard of them?

200
00:12:05.324 --> 00:12:07.175
All they handle is
death penalty cases.

201
00:12:07.243 --> 00:12:08.604
There's a guy there. Ben Forsik.

202
00:12:08.628 --> 00:12:09.939
I sent him copies
of everything I had.

203
00:12:09.963 --> 00:12:11.890
I mean. you can go there.
tell him what you found.

204
00:12:11.914 --> 00:12:14.215
Maybe. it'll be enough
to bring them on board.

205
00:12:14.817 --> 00:12:15.916
Okay.

206
00:12:19.606 --> 00:12:21.939
So. how's Sebastian?

207
00:12:23.927 --> 00:12:25.193
What do you mean?

208
00:12:26.279 --> 00:12:28.345
Well. you being here. I mean.

209
00:12:29.382 --> 00:12:30.597
is he cool with it?

210
00:12:32.369 --> 00:12:34.468
I haven't talked to him.

211
00:12:36.189 --> 00:12:37.705
The. um.

212
00:12:38.475 --> 00:12:39.974
engagement's off.

213
00:12:41.077 --> 00:12:42.510
Oh.

214
00:12:42.578 --> 00:12:44.945
Sorry.

215
00:12:45.015 --> 00:12:47.482
You could at least say
that like you mean it.

216
00:12:48.451 --> 00:12:49.550
I do.

217
00:12:52.055 --> 00:12:54.521
God. you always
were a lousy liar.

218
00:12:55.625 --> 00:12:56.890
Hmm.

219
00:12:56.959 --> 00:12:57.959
Yeah.

220
00:13:00.714 --> 00:13:02.847
I'd better get to
Project Justice.

221
00:13:12.725 --> 00:13:13.774
Veronica.

222
00:13:17.998 --> 00:13:19.063
Thank you.

223
00:13:20.200 --> 00:13:21.960
I didn't have a whole lot left.

224
00:13:21.984 --> 00:13:24.352
You can thank me when
I get you out of here.

225
00:13:29.375 --> 00:13:30.657
(DOOR BUZZING)

226
00:13:30.726 --> 00:13:31.859
(DOOR OPENS)

227
00:13:36.399 --> 00:13:37.564
(DOOR CLOSES)

228
00:13:41.888 --> 00:13:43.587
Baby. it's me. Are you there?

229
00:13:45.058 --> 00:13:46.557
Hello? Are you there?

230
00:13:46.625 --> 00:13:49.894
Hey. if she is. she obviously
don't want to talk to you.

231
00:13:49.963 --> 00:13:51.128
(PRISONERS CHATTERING)

232
00:13:51.197 --> 00:13:53.197
PRISONER: That dude
right there. right there.

233
00:13:53.266 --> 00:13:54.598
It's Wednesday. babe.

234
00:13:54.667 --> 00:13:56.948
You're gonna come
around today. right?

235
00:13:57.570 --> 00:13:59.070
Look. I gotta hang up now.

236
00:13:59.138 --> 00:14:01.038
I gotta go back in the block.

237
00:14:01.107 --> 00:14:03.388
but you're gonna
be here today. right?

238
00:14:04.244 --> 00:14:06.484
I'm your man.
baby. and I love you.

239
00:14:07.046 --> 00:14:08.145
I do.

240
00:14:11.017 --> 00:14:12.937
<i>(MAN CHATTERING ON LOUDSPEAKER)</i>

241
00:14:14.604 --> 00:14:16.504
(INMATES CHATTERING)

242
00:14:24.147 --> 00:14:25.496
It's a pattern.

243
00:14:26.666 --> 00:14:28.149
What did you say?

244
00:14:28.217 --> 00:14:30.384
Your tattoo. it's a pattern.

245
00:14:30.453 --> 00:14:31.802
You're seeing things.

246
00:14:40.313 --> 00:14:42.830
Putting him in with Haywire
is a low blow. Deputy.

247
00:14:42.899 --> 00:14:45.816
What? The shrinks cleared
Haywire for reentry into Gen Pop.

248
00:14:45.885 --> 00:14:47.618
Besides. he's so
doped up on meds.

249
00:14:47.687 --> 00:14:49.181
he's like a kitten these days.

250
00:14:49.205 --> 00:14:50.949
A kitten who murdered
both his parents.

251
00:14:50.973 --> 00:14:52.390
With all due respect. sir.

252
00:14:52.459 --> 00:14:54.776
if you give Scofield
preferential treatment.

253
00:14:54.844 --> 00:14:57.361
it'll undermine
your credibility.

254
00:14:57.430 --> 00:14:59.492
Look. I know you got
a soft spot for the guy

255
00:14:59.516 --> 00:15:01.010
because he's got
brains in his head.

256
00:15:01.034 --> 00:15:03.412
and he's helping you with
that contraption in there.

257
00:15:03.436 --> 00:15:05.364
But the guy's a
violent criminal.

258
00:15:05.388 --> 00:15:08.099
He deserves punishment just
as much as the rest of these guys.

259
00:15:08.123 --> 00:15:09.635
You have been here
long enough to know

260
00:15:09.659 --> 00:15:11.337
that I'm less interested
in punishment

261
00:15:11.361 --> 00:15:12.727
than I am in rehabilitation.

262
00:15:12.795 --> 00:15:14.206
And sticking him in with Haywire

263
00:15:14.230 --> 00:15:16.397
is not rehabilitation
in my book.

264
00:15:16.465 --> 00:15:18.961
You delegated authority
over Gen Pop to me. boss.

265
00:15:18.985 --> 00:15:20.017
I know I did.

