00:29:44.049 --> 00:29:46.566
<i>10 minutes. Lights
out in 10 minutes.</i>

524
00:30:17.199 --> 00:30:19.711
What stood out for me was
that most death penalty cases

525
00:30:19.735 --> 00:30:22.035
take 10 years to
exhaust all appeals.

526
00:30:22.103 --> 00:30:24.137
Lincoln got there in three.

527
00:30:24.206 --> 00:30:25.772
So for it to be expedited.

528
00:30:25.841 --> 00:30:28.386
there had to have been some
sort of political influence. right?

529
00:30:28.410 --> 00:30:31.373
Well. given that Terrence Steadman
is the Vice President's brother.

530
00:30:31.397 --> 00:30:32.674
that's not too hard to believe.

531
00:30:32.698 --> 00:30:34.326
How. though? They
got to every judge

532
00:30:34.350 --> 00:30:35.793
that rejected Lincoln's appeal?

533
00:30:35.817 --> 00:30:37.350
It doesn't take a judge.

534
00:30:38.954 --> 00:30:42.555
All it takes is a little special
attention from one of his clerks.

535
00:30:42.625 --> 00:30:44.035
But how Lincoln got fast-tracked

536
00:30:44.059 --> 00:30:45.987
doesn't interest me. It's why.

537
00:30:46.011 --> 00:30:48.278
If he was set up. then why?

538
00:30:48.347 --> 00:30:51.881
I think the answer to
that might lie in the victim.

539
00:30:51.950 --> 00:30:54.700
What do we know? That he
was the CEO of Ecofield. right?

540
00:30:54.769 --> 00:30:56.586
That he was pushing
alternative energy.

541
00:30:56.655 --> 00:30:58.850
Successfully pushing
alternative energy.

542
00:30:58.874 --> 00:31:02.692
So oil companies. the Saudis.
even our own government.

543
00:31:02.761 --> 00:31:04.088
a lot of people stood to benefit

544
00:31:04.112 --> 00:31:06.272
with Steadman
out of the picture.

545
00:31:07.616 --> 00:31:10.867
Why did you wait till
now to take up this case?

546
00:31:10.936 --> 00:31:13.170
I thought he did it.
like everybody else.

547
00:31:14.840 --> 00:31:16.956
I just hope it's not too late.

548
00:31:17.025 --> 00:31:18.725
It very well may be.

549
00:31:18.794 --> 00:31:20.754
You need to prepare
yourself for that.

550
00:31:23.365 --> 00:31:24.964
What about you?

551
00:31:26.018 --> 00:31:27.617
Why death penalty work?

552
00:31:29.938 --> 00:31:32.973
My father did 15 years for
a crime he didn't commit.

553
00:31:33.041 --> 00:31:36.042
I know firsthand that when the
government gets you in their crosshairs

554
00:31:36.111 --> 00:31:37.577
you stand very little chance.

555
00:31:38.279 --> 00:31:39.412
That's why.

556
00:31:43.535 --> 00:31:45.535
Now. do you want my help?

557
00:31:47.505 --> 00:31:49.055
(PRISONERS CHATTERING)

558
00:32:10.211 --> 00:32:11.705
I want back in. Too late.

559
00:32:11.729 --> 00:32:13.607
I'll do anything you
need. See these hands?

560
00:32:13.631 --> 00:32:15.043
They're digging
machines. You want to go

561
00:32:15.067 --> 00:32:16.544
to China? I'll get
you to China. Fish.

562
00:32:16.568 --> 00:32:18.646
I'll dig like a psychotic
rodent if I have to.

563
00:32:18.670 --> 00:32:20.570
Fish. I gotta be back in.

564
00:32:20.639 --> 00:32:22.617
As of right now. there is no in.

565
00:32:22.641 --> 00:32:24.552
Van Gogh over there's
my new cellmate.

566
00:32:24.576 --> 00:32:26.387
But you're gonna do
something about it. right?

567
00:32:26.411 --> 00:32:28.862
You're gonna get rid of
him. I'll do what's necessary.

568
00:32:28.931 --> 00:32:30.196
You're my boy.

569
00:32:30.265 --> 00:32:31.615
(LAUGHING)

570
00:32:33.435 --> 00:32:34.834
So. how you gonna do it?

571
00:32:34.903 --> 00:32:36.853
Well. let's just
put it this way.

572
00:32:36.921 --> 00:32:38.321
Someone's going to get hurt.

573
00:32:41.209 --> 00:32:42.692
<i>(PHONE RINGING)</i>

574
00:32:47.432 --> 00:32:49.159
WOMAN: How did
we miss this. guys?

575
00:32:49.183 --> 00:32:52.313
Scofield's father was out of the
picture by the time he was born.

576
00:32:52.337 --> 00:32:53.965
He took his mother's
maiden name.

577
00:32:53.989 --> 00:32:55.938
All right. Scofield
had no priors

578
00:32:56.007 --> 00:32:57.952
and a full-time
job as an engineer.

579
00:32:57.976 --> 00:32:59.008
<i>KELLERMAN: Correct.</i>

580
00:32:59.077 --> 00:33:00.905
Then he goes and robs a bank.

581
00:33:00.929 --> 00:33:03.229
discharging a gun in the process

582
00:33:03.298 --> 00:33:06.360
so that at sentencing he could
maneuver his way to Fox River

583
00:33:06.384 --> 00:33:09.797
<i>where his brother's scheduled
to die in less than a month.</i>

584
00:33:09.821 --> 00:33:11.454
<i>Obviously. something's up.</i>

585
00:33:11.523 --> 00:33:12.989
With all due respect.

586
00:33:13.058 --> 00:33:15.770
brothers are incarcerated
together all over the country.

587
00:33:15.794 --> 00:33:17.744
It may just be a coincidence.

588
00:33:17.813 --> 00:33:19.613
Move on the younger brother.

589
00:33:19.681 --> 00:33:22.382
Do it preemptively
before anything rises up.

590
00:33:22.451 --> 00:33:24.317
bites any of us in the ass.

591
00:33:25.821 --> 00:33:27.349
GUARD: All right.
let's move it along!

592
00:33:27.373 --> 00:33:28.438
Let's look alive!

593
00:33:38.199 --> 00:33:39.399
It's a pathway.

594
00:33:40.819 --> 00:33:42.068
Where does it lead?

595
00:33:44.690 --> 00:33:46.139
Where are you taking me?

596
00:33:52.714 --> 00:33:53.997
What are you. nuts?

597
00:33:55.784 --> 00:33:57.134
Officer!

598
00:33:57.202 --> 00:33:59.018
I need an officer!

599
00:33:59.087 --> 00:34:00.203
Shut up!

600
00:34:00.271 --> 00:34:02.366
What the hell's the
problem down here?

601
00:34:02.390 --> 00:34:04.357
What? Son of a bitch.

602
00:34:04.426 --> 00:34:06.559
Open up on 40.

603
00:34:06.628 --> 00:34:09.713
He's got the pathway on
his body. It leads somewhere.

604
00:34:09.782 --> 00:34:11.064
Back off. Haywire.

605
00:34:11.133 --> 00:34:13.884
No. look. Look at his
tattoos. It's a pathway.

606
00:34:13.952 --> 00:34:16.285
Haywire. I said back
off. You want a hot shot?

607
00:34:16.354 --> 00:34:17.554
I'm telling you. look at...

608
00:34:18.206 --> 00:34:19.339
Back off!

609
00:34:20.342 --> 00:34:21.441
Let's go!

610
00:34:22.961 --> 00:34:25.089
Get him out of
here! It leads to hell!

611
00:34:25.113 --> 00:34:27.413
It's a pathway to hell!

612
00:34:27.482 --> 00:34:29.716
He's taking us all to hell!

613
00:34:41.863 --> 00:34:43.279
(BUZZING)

614
00:34:47.686 --> 00:34:50.720
So. the gang's all
back together again.

615
00:34:50.789 --> 00:34:53.457
Well. ain't that swell?

616
00:34:53.525 --> 00:34:56.059
Told you not to go
around me to the Pope.

617
00:34:56.127 --> 00:34:58.927
But you just keep
making waves. don't you?

618
00:35:08.139 --> 00:35:10.540
Good to be back. man.
Good to have you back.

619
00:35:15.514 --> 00:35:17.914
So. when do we get started?

620
00:35:46.327 --> 00:35:48.194
Good afternoon. Mr. Scofield.

621
00:35:48.263 --> 00:35:49.395
MICHAEL: Hello.

622
00:35:50.265 --> 00:35:51.731
How you feeling today?

623
00:35:52.567 --> 00:35:53.800
Pretty good.

624
00:35:55.737 --> 00:35:56.937
What happened?

625
00:35:58.156 --> 00:35:59.589
Uh.

626
00:35:59.658 --> 00:36:01.674
caught an elbow
playing basketball.

627
00:36:02.794 --> 00:36:03.926
Uh-huh.

628
00:36:05.864 --> 00:36:07.380
Mind if I take a look?

629
00:36:07.448 --> 00:36:08.632
By all means.

630
00:36:17.692 --> 00:36:19.993
You know you're going
to get killed in here. right.

631
00:36:20.061 --> 00:36:21.528
if you're not careful?

632
00:36:23.732 --> 00:36:25.131
I'll make you a bet.

633
00:36:26.034 --> 00:36:28.301
When I get out of here alive.

634
00:36:29.738 --> 00:36:31.254
I'll take you to dinner.

635
00:36:33.608 --> 00:36:35.758
Lunch. Cup of coffee.

636
00:36:35.827 --> 00:36:37.494
Michael. this um.

637
00:36:37.563 --> 00:36:39.913
this charm act

638
00:36:39.982 --> 00:36:42.983
could be exactly what's getting
you into trouble out in the yard.

639
00:36:48.440 --> 00:36:49.672
Lean forward.

640
00:37:01.286 --> 00:37:02.335
All right.

641
00:37:02.403 --> 00:37:03.781
so you went to
the parking garage.

642
00:37:03.805 --> 00:37:06.005
Terrence Steadman
is already dead.

643
00:37:06.341 --> 00:37:07.485
That's right.

644
00:37:07.509 --> 00:37:09.776
You saw that. and
you ran. Took the gun.

645
00:37:09.845 --> 00:37:11.027
Dumped the gun.

646
00:37:11.096 --> 00:37:12.373
Where? Storm drain.

647
00:37:12.397 --> 00:37:13.591
Van Buren and Wells.

648
00:37:13.615 --> 00:37:15.582
Nobody ever found it.

649
00:37:15.650 --> 00:37:17.350
What do you do after that?

650
00:37:17.418 --> 00:37:19.179
You go back to your apartment?

651
00:37:19.203 --> 00:37:20.219
Yeah.

652
00:37:23.191 --> 00:37:26.592
<i>I was freaking out. trying to
figure out what had happened.</i>

653
00:37:26.661 --> 00:37:29.361
<i>Then I saw the
bloody pants in the tub.</i>

654
00:37:33.101 --> 00:37:36.002
The cops. they busted in
a minute after I got there.

655
00:37:36.071 --> 00:37:38.616
The pants. the ones with
Steadman's blood on them.

656
00:37:38.640 --> 00:37:42.191
First cop on the scene says he
saw you washing them in the bathtub.

657
00:37:42.243 --> 00:37:45.928
He's lying. My hands were wet
after splashing water on my face.

658
00:37:45.997 --> 00:37:48.237
Police! Let's see
your hands! Hands up!

659
00:37:49.584 --> 00:37:52.034
I never touched those pants.

660
00:37:52.103 --> 00:37:53.547
Which brings us back to the gun.

661
00:37:53.571 --> 00:37:55.021
The one you said you dumped.

662
00:37:55.090 --> 00:37:57.668
It was planted. It's the only
way it could've got there.

663
00:37:57.692 --> 00:37:59.620
Ballistics matched
it to a slug that was...

664
00:37:59.644 --> 00:38:01.539
The gun was
planted. it was planted.

665
00:38:01.563 --> 00:38:03.179
Just like the pants.

666
00:38:03.248 --> 00:38:05.565
Your fingerprints
were all over the gun.

667
00:38:09.454 --> 00:38:10.553
Bo.

668
00:38:15.126 --> 00:38:16.325
Who's Bo?

669
00:38:16.394 --> 00:38:18.634
He's the guy who
arranged everything.

670
00:38:20.749 --> 00:38:22.527
<i>Had me come around
the night before.</i>

671
00:38:22.551 --> 00:38:24.884
<i>tried a few guns. see
which one felt right.</i>

672
00:38:24.953 --> 00:38:26.681
<i>And that was the
setup right there.</i>

673
00:38:26.705 --> 00:38:28.482
<i>One of those must've
been the murder weapon.</i>

674
00:38:28.506 --> 00:38:31.068
Then that's how they got
my fingerprints on the gun.

675
00:38:31.092 --> 00:38:32.258
Had to be.

676
00:38:33.478 --> 00:38:35.622
NICK: All right.
so this... this Bo.

677
00:38:35.646 --> 00:38:37.406
uh. he coerces
you into doing this.

678
00:38:37.449 --> 00:38:39.215
all to clear a $90.000 debt?

679
00:38:41.002 --> 00:38:42.669
He was gonna kill my son.

680
00:38:43.738 --> 00:38:45.288
Well?

681
00:38:45.357 --> 00:38:47.702
A lot of "I didn't do its." and
those don't count for much.

682
00:38:47.726 --> 00:38:50.526
The security tape. the one that
shows Lincoln pulling the trigger.

683
00:38:50.562 --> 00:38:52.039
you've got it. right? Yeah.

684
00:38:52.063 --> 00:38:54.225
If Lincoln's telling the
truth. then that tape is lying.

685
00:38:54.249 --> 00:38:57.329
I think we should have a
look. Decide for ourselves.

686
00:39:04.392 --> 00:39:05.608
You're clear.

687
00:39:22.527 --> 00:39:25.473
If the chemicals can eat
through the iron pipes.

688
00:39:25.497 --> 00:39:28.092
how come they can't eat
through the toothpaste tube?

689
00:39:28.116 --> 00:39:29.960
It's only when the
chemicals are combined

690
00:39:29.984 --> 00:39:31.868
that they become a corrosive.

691
00:39:31.936 --> 00:39:33.847
You studied chemistry
or something?

692
00:39:33.871 --> 00:39:35.155
Not in school.

693
00:39:51.473 --> 00:39:54.185
But what you're doing
up there in the infirmary.

694
00:39:54.209 --> 00:39:56.642
what has that got to do
with what we're doing here?

695
00:39:56.711 --> 00:39:59.645
Getting through this
wall is just the beginning.

696
00:39:59.714 --> 00:40:01.180
There's a whole
lot of real estate

697
00:40:01.249 --> 00:40:03.816
in between here
and the outside walls.

698
00:40:03.885 --> 00:40:06.769
The infirmary's the closest
building to those walls.

699
00:40:13.111 --> 00:40:15.544
And the weakest link
in the security chain.

700
00:40:15.981 --> 00:40:17.246
Cool.

701
00:40:23.521 --> 00:40:27.157
I think I've removed
enough grout to bust through.

702
00:40:27.225 --> 00:40:29.458
I'm going to need you
to make some noise.

703
00:40:35.683 --> 00:40:37.951
(SINGING IN SPANISH)

704
00:40:40.555 --> 00:40:42.221
Is that the best you can do?

705
00:40:43.708 --> 00:40:45.542
Have some faith. <i>papi.</i>

706
00:40:45.610 --> 00:40:47.376
have some faith.

707
00:40:47.446 --> 00:40:49.145
(SINGING IN SPANISH)

708
00:40:50.232 --> 00:40:51.413
INMATE: Shut up!

709
00:40:54.235 --> 00:40:55.751
(INMATES CHATTERING)

710
00:41:00.909 --> 00:41:02.008
(BUZZING)

711
00:41:03.177 --> 00:41:04.610
(SUCRE SINGING IN SPANISH)

712
00:41:34.693 --> 00:41:36.358
INMATE: Shut up!

713
00:41:36.427 --> 00:41:38.911
Not one more word!

714
00:41:38.980 --> 00:41:42.460
Next inmate that opens
his mouth goes in the hole!

715
00:41:57.198 --> 00:41:58.347
We're good.

716
00:42:25.994 --> 00:42:27.160
You okay?

717
00:42:30.982 --> 00:42:32.148
Work.

718
00:42:33.384 --> 00:42:34.450
It's fine.

719
00:42:34.518 --> 00:42:35.785
(DOORBELL RINGS)

720
00:42:37.922 --> 00:42:39.055
I got it.

721
00:42:43.978 --> 00:42:46.829
Everything all right?
Couldn't be better.

722
00:42:46.897 --> 00:42:49.665
Do you want to come in?
We just sat down to eat.

723
00:42:49.734 --> 00:42:52.251
No. I just wanted to stop
by to tell you in person.

724
00:42:55.372 --> 00:42:56.639
Problem solved.

725
00:42:57.408 --> 00:42:58.875
What's this?

726
00:42:58.944 --> 00:43:01.077
That is a transfer request.

727
00:43:01.145 --> 00:43:03.112
Michael Scofield is
getting shipped out

728
00:43:03.815 --> 00:43:04.948
tomorrow.

729
00:43:09.937 --> 00:43:11.087
Have a good night.

729
